6. Booster Fusion Algorithm

6.1 Model Predictive Control (MPC) for Transition

The transition between loiter (electric, wings extended) and sprint (ramjet, wings swept) is governed by MPC.

System Model:

· State: x = [position, velocity, attitude, wing sweep angle, engine mode]
· Control: u = [throttle electric, throttle ramjet, thrust vector angles, wing sweep rate]

Cost Function:
J = Σ (w1 * ||x - x_ref||^2 + w2 * ||u||^2 + w3 * transition_time_penalty)

Constraints:

· Actuator limits, structural loads (from Engineering Algorithm), no‑fly zones

Solver:

· Real‑time iteration (RTI) using ACADO toolkit or Forces PRO.
· Solved at 50 Hz.

6.2 Aerodynamic Model Learning

A Gaussian Process (GP) regression model learns aerodynamic coefficients from flight data and updates the MPC internal model online, improving accuracy over time.

GP Input: α (angle of attack), β (sideslip), Mach number, wing sweep
Output: CL, CD, Cm

6.3 Transition Logic

High‑level trigger from Gabriel initiates transition. MPC then computes optimal trajectory to new mode.

