7. Hybrid Photonic‑Electronic AI

7.1 Photonic Processing Primitives

The photonic core performs optical matrix‑vector multiplications using Mach‑Zehnder interferometer arrays.

Primitives:

· photonic_matmul(A, B): Computes C = A * B optically, with A and B encoded in amplitude/phase.
· photonic_conv(image, kernel): 2D convolution via Fourier optics.
· photonic_fft(signal): Optical FFT.

These are exposed via a low‑level API to the electronic processor.

7.2 Task Partitioning

· Photonic: Raw sensor data filtering, image preprocessing, radar pulse compression, FFTs.
· Electronic: High‑level fusion, control, communication, ethical reasoning.

Scheduler:
A lightweight runtime on the electronic core dispatches tasks to the photonic core via a shared memory queue. Synchronisation is achieved with hardware semaphores.

7.3 Interconnect Protocol

High‑speed optical SerDes links (100 Gbps) connect the two domains. Data is transferred in pinned buffers with zero‑copy.

