8. Engineering Algorithm

8.1 Real‑Time Structural Health Monitoring

Fiber‑optic sensors (Bragg gratings) measure strain at critical points. The algorithm:

· Computes current stress distribution from strain using finite element model (FEM).
· Detects anomalies (e.g., sudden strain changes indicating crack growth).
· Updates FEM parameters to match observed strains (inverse problem solved via gradient descent).

8.2 Fatigue Life Prediction

Uses Miner’s rule with rainflow counting of stress cycles. Crack growth is modelled by Paris law:

da/dN = C (ΔK)^m

where ΔK is stress intensity factor range, C and m material constants.

Output: Remaining useful life (flight hours) and safe load limits.

8.3 Adaptation

If damage is detected, the Engineering Algorithm advises the Booster Fusion Algorithm to reduce load factors or speed, and alerts Rafael.

