9. Quantum Algorithm

9.1 Quantum Key Distribution (BB84)

Implemented using a free‑space optical transceiver.

Process:

1. Ground station sends polarized photons (four states).
2. UAV measures in random bases.
3. Public discussion (classical channel) to sift key.
4. Error correction and privacy amplification (Cascade + Toeplitz hashing).

Key rate: ~1 Mbps at 100 km range.

9.2 Trajectory Optimisation as QUBO

Intercept trajectory optimisation is cast as a Quadratic Unconstrained Binary Optimisation (QUBO) problem and solved on a quantum annealer.

Formulation:

· Discretise time into N steps.
· Binary variables x_{i,j} indicate whether the interceptor is at grid point (i,j) at time step t.
· Objective: minimise distance to target at final time, subject to motion constraints.
· QUBO matrix is constructed and submitted to the quantum processor.

Fallback: If quantum solution not available, use classical mixed‑integer programming solver (Gurobi).

9.3 Quantum Random Number Generator

On‑chip quantum random number generator (based on shot noise) provides true randomness for cryptographic keys and mission‑critical stochastic decisions.

