10. Linux Core Algorithm

10.1 Real‑Time Scheduling

· Kernel compiled with PREEMPT_RT patch.
· Critical tasks (flight control at 1 kHz, sensor sampling at 100 Hz) assigned FIFO priority 99.
· Non‑critical AI tasks run in SCHED_OTHER with cgroup CPU limits.

10.2 Container Isolation

Each QUENNE layer runs in a separate Docker container. cgroups enforce CPU, memory, and I/O limits. Namespaces provide isolation.

10.3 Security Modules

· SELinux in enforcing mode with custom policy for each container.
· Integrity Measurement Architecture (IMA) verifies file hashes at runtime.
· Secure boot with UEFI and signed kernel.

