11. Cross‑Platform Abstraction

11.1 Hardware Abstraction Layer (HAL)

Provides uniform API for:

· Sensor drivers (read(), configure())
· Actuator interfaces (set_position(), set_throttle())
· Timing (get_time_us())

HAL implementation uses board support packages for each target architecture (ARM, x86, RISC‑V).

11.2 Middleware – DDS

All inter‑process communication uses DDS (Eclipse Cyclone DDS). Topics defined for:

· Sensor data streams
· Track objects
· Commands
· Health status

QoS settings ensure reliability for critical topics.

11.3 ROS2 Nodes

For simulation and prototyping, ROS2 nodes wrap the DDS topics, allowing easy integration with standard tools (RViz, rqt).

